details.purpose: Intended to capture the 5-item version of the International Index of Erectile Function (IIEF-5) as a diagnostic tool for erectile dysfunction.
details.use: Use to record 5-item scoring test for erectile dysfunction.

items.items: A specific date and/or time which may be explicitly defined in a template or at run-time.
Confidence to get and keep erection.
Prompt: Over the past 6 months how did you rate your confidence that you could get and keep an erection?
Over past 6 months confidence of ability to get and keep erection is very low.
Over past 6 months confidence of ability to get and keep erection is low.
Over the past 6 months confidence of ability to get and keep erection is moderate.
Over the past 6 months confidence of ability to get and keep erection is high.
Over the past 6 months confidence of ability to get and keep erection is very high.
Frequency of erection being hard enough for penetration.

Prompt: Over the past 6 months when you had erections with sexual stimulation, how often were your erections hard enough for penetration? with sexual stimulation, how often were your erections hard enough for penetration? with sexual stimulation, how often were your erections hard enough for penetration?
There was no sexual activity over the past 6 months.
Over the past 6 months erections were almost never or never hard enough for penetration.
Over the past 6 months erections were hard enough for penetration a few times.
Over the past 6 months erections were sometimes hard enough for penetration.
Over the past 6 months erections were hard enough for penetration most times.
Over the past 6 months erections were almost always or always hard enough for penetration.
Frequency of erection being maintained after penetration.
Prompt: Over the past 6 months during sexual intercourse, how often were you able to maintain your erection after you had penetrated your partner?
Over the past 6 months intercourse was not attempted.
Over the past 6 months erection was almost never or never maintained after penetration.
Over the past 6 months erection was maintained after penetration a few times.
Over the past 6 months erection was sometimes maintained after penetration.
Over the past 6 months erection was maintained after penetration most times.
Over the past 6 months erection was almost always or always maintained after penetration.
Frequency of erection being maintained to completion of intercourse.
Prompt: Over the past 6 months during sexual intercourse, how difficult was it to maintain your erection to completion of intercourse?
Over the past 6 months intercourse was not attempted.
Over the past 6 months it was extremely difficult to maintain erections to completion of intercourse.
Over the past 6 months it was very difficult to maintain erections to completion of intercourse.
Over the past 6 months it was difficult to maintain erections to completion of intercourse.
Over the past 6 months it was slightly difficult to maintain erections to completion of intercourse.
Over the past 6 months it was not difficult to maintain erections to completion of intercourse.
Frequency of satisfactory outcome of intercourse.
Prompt: Over the last 6 months when you attempted sexual intercourse, how often was it satisfactory to you?
Over the past 6 months intercourse was not attempted.
Over the past 6 months intercourse was almost never or never satisfactory.
Over the past 6 months intercourse was satisfactory a few times.
Over the past 6 months intercourse was sometimes satisfactory.
Over the past 6 months intercourse was satisfactory most times.
Over the past 6 months intercourse was almost always or always satisfactory.

The IIEF-5 is administered as a screening instrument for the presence & severity of ED in conjunction with the clinical assessment. The score is the sum of the responses to the five items, so that overall score may range from 1 to 25. A score of 20 or higher indicates a normal degree of erectile functioning. Low scores (10 or less) indicate moderate to severe ED.
Description of any incidental factors that may have contributed to the score.
